id: pm-5rjn
title: Continuous governance automation and policy enforcement
description: "Productize tracker-governance workflows so normalization, placeholder detection, and large-scale policy enforcement can run deterministically without ad-hoc scripts."
type: Epic
status: open
priority: 1
tags[4]: automation,governance,pm-cli,traceability
created_at: "2026-04-04T21:54:42.936Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-04T21:58:02.822Z"
deadline: "2026-04-25T21:54:42.936Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 360
acceptance_criteria: "Governance automation roadmap includes deterministic normalization/reporting capabilities, validation checks for low-signal metadata, and safe operational workflows that reduce manual force-override churn while preserving ownership semantics."
definition_of_ready: Existing governance baseline metrics and pain points are documented from recent tracker sweep.
goal: Governance operations by default
objective: Replace manual sweeps with repeatable command-level workflows
value: Cuts governance maintenance cost and improves consistency
impact: Reduces manual mutation risk and accelerates future tracker cleanup
outcome: Future agents can run governance upkeep through supported pm surfaces
why_now: Current standards-alignment required long scripted passes and ownership remediations that should be converted into productized workflows.
reviewer: maintainer-review
risk: medium
confidence: medium
sprint: governance-followups
release: vnext
reporter: codex-agent
severity: medium
environment: linux
repro_steps: Re-run full tracker normalization manually and observe script-heavy operational burden.
affected_version: 2026.3.12
component: governance-automation
regression: false
customer_impact: "Maintainers and agents gain safer, faster, and more deterministic governance maintenance."
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:54:42.936Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'bulk governance normalization command pm tracker' --limit 20; pm search 'validate placeholder metadata blocked_reason unblock_note repro_steps' --limit 20; pm search 'ownership-safe batch mutation mode governance override' --limit 20; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Net-new because existing governance epics are historical execution snapshots rather than productized automation roadmap."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-04T21:54:42.936Z",codex-agent,"Roadmap will prioritize dry-run visibility,deterministic mutation plans,and safety semantics compatible with ownership and lock constraints."
